Write HTML code to display text formatting tags like(b,strong,I,em,q,blockquote,del,ins,font,pre,code,tt,html entities,sub,sup).
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Formatting Tags</title>
</head>
<body>
    <ul>
        <li> <b>This is bold text</b></li>
        <li> <strong>This is strong text</strong></li>
        <li> <i>This is italic text</i></li>
        <li> <em>This is emphasized text</em></li>
        <li> <q>This is quotation</q></li>
        <li> <blockquote>This is a blockquote</blockquote></li>
        <li> <del>This text is deleted</del></li>   
        <li> <ins>This text is inserted</ins></li>
        <li> <font color="red">This is red text</font></li>
        <li> <pre>This is preformatted text</pre></li>
        <li> <code>This is code text</code></li>
        <li> <tt>This is teletype text</tt></li>
        <li> HTML entities: &amp; &lt; &gt; &quot; &apos;</li>
        <li> <sub>This is subscript text</sub></li>
        <li> <sup>This is superscript text</sup></li>
        
    </ul>
</body>
</html>
